The paper deals with optimization problems in multiantenna broadcast and interference channels, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of linear beamforming strategies also suggests a possible connection to Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed Branch-and-Bound method and the comparison of suboptimal techniques with global optimal solutions may be relevant to Machine Learning (cs.LG).
